    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> roughly, peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped mushrooms </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until browned</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Push the mushrooms and shallot to one side of the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until lightly browned</p><p>Once lightly browned, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>with 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-14 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst your sauce is cooking, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta<strong> </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta<strong> </strong>and return to the pot</p><p>Whilst the pasta is cooking, grate your<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken cooked, transfer the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken </strong>to the pan and add the <strong>drained pasta</strong></p><p>Tear in <strong>half </strong>the<strong> basil</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Gently stir it all together until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> spicy chicken & mushroom arrabbiata</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chicken-and-mushroom-arrabbiata-with-basil/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy chicken & mushroom arrabbiata </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining basil</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
